data.text: 1. Henry Schnepp-1. Esther Schaub. Register Report for Henry Schnepp Generation 1 Henry Schnepp and Esther Schaub. They had 2 children. 2. i. Sarah Maria Schnepp [1]. She was born on 8 May 1833 in near Dayton, Montgomery Co., OH [2]. She married Johann Paul Dreiser. They were married on 1 Jan 1851 in near Piqua, Ohio [3]. She died on 14 Nov 1890 in Chicago, Cook Co., IL [4]. 3. ii. Esther A. Schnepp [5]. She was born May 1840 in Ohio (Dayton, Montgomery Co.?) [6, 7, 8]. She married David Parks. They were married Aft. 1859 in Ohio? Kansas? [9, 7, 10]. She died on 24 Aug 1916 in Seattle, WA [11, 5]. Burial in Mount Pleasant Cemetery, Seattle, WA [5]. Generation 2 2. Sarah Maria Schnepp-2 (Henry Schnepp-1) [1]. She was born on 8 May 1833 in near Dayton, Montgomery Co., OH [2]. She died on 14 Nov 1890 in Chicago, Cook Co., IL [4]. Johann Paul Dreiser is the son of John Dreiser and Cathrine Acher. He was born on 9 Sep 1821 in Mayen, Germany [2, 12]. Emigration 1844. He died on 25 Dec 1900 in Rochester, Monroe Co., NY [13]. Burial on 29 Dec 1900 in Chicago, Ill.. He was also known as Paul. Johann Paul Dreiser and Sarah Maria Schnepp. They were married on 1 Jan 1851 in near Piqua, Ohio [3]. They had 13 children. i. child. ii. child. iii. child. iv. John Paul Dresser Jr.. He was born on 22 Apr 1858 in Terre Haute, Clay Co., IN. Baptism on 24 May 1858 in St. Joseph University Parish, Terre Haute [14]. Burial on 2 Feb 1906 in Calvary Cemetery, Long Island, N.Y.. He was also known as Paul. He died in New York, NY [15]. v. Markus Romanus Dreiser. He was born on 12 Feb 1860 in Terre Haute, Clay Co., IN [16]. Baptism on 26 Feb 1860 in St Joseph University Parish, Terre Haute, IN [17]. He died on 21 Mar 1940 in Metropolitan Hospital, Welfare Island, New York, NY. He was also known as Rome. 4. vi. Maria Franziska Dreiser. She was born on 7 Jul 1861 in Terre Haute, Clay Co., IN [18]. Baptism on 14 Jul 1861 in St Joseph University Parish, Terre Haute, IN [19]. She married Austin Daniel Brennan. They were married 1883 in Chicago, Cook Co., IL. She died on 2 Jun 1944 in Queens, NY [18, 20]. She was also known as Mame. Cause of Death was cancer of the bladder. Page 1 of 12 Thursday, September 04, 2008 3:09:58 PM
